@Node SYPNOSIS "Rotor/Sypnosis"

@{b}NAME@{ub}
   SYS:WBStartup/Rotor

@{b}Sypnosis@{ub}
   Rotor
      @{"CX_PRIORITY/N/K    " Link TOOLTYPES 5}  =<System Priority>
      @{"CX_POPKEY/K        " Link TOOLTYPES 13}  =<@{"Hot Key Description String" Link HOTKEY}>
      @{"CX_POPUP/S         " Link TOOLTYPES 7}  =<YES | NO>
      @{"BLANKKEY/K         " Link TOOLTYPES 17}  =<@{"Hot Key Description String" Link HOTKEY}>
      @{"SECONDS=TIMEOUT/N/K" Link TOOLTYPES 21}  =<1 - 3600>
      @{"CLIENTTIMEOUT/N/K  " Link TOOLTYPES 27}  =<1 - 60>
      @{"DISPLAY/K          " Link TOOLTYPES 33}  =<@{"Display Description String" Link DISPLAY}>
      @{"CYCLE/S            " Link TOOLTYPES 38}  =<YES | NO>
      @{"MOUSEBLANKMETHOD/K " Link TOOLTYPES 39}  =<Hardware | FreeSprite>
      @{"CHANGE/N/K         " Link TOOLTYPES 47}  =<1 - 200>
      @{"TRAIL/N/K          " Link TOOLTYPES 52}  =<1 - 200>

@EndNode

@Node DESCRIPTION "Rotor/Description"
@{b}Description@{ub}
   A Screenblanker with high security which does not burn
   in the graphic into the screen when CPU is really busy.
   It's funny to watch, runs @{i}only@{ui} under Amiga OS Release 2.04 or newer.

   Rotor was inspired by a flightsimulator. The routine which was used to
   simulate the spinning rotor of a plane is use in this blanker.

   The effects are somewhat mesmerizing and spindizzy.

@EndNode

@Node SOURCE "Rotor/Source"
@{b}Source@{ub}
    The source code is included, it can be compiled with SAS-C 5.10a
    (or newer) or with the registered version of Dice V2.06.40 (or newer).

    The source is included to give you a chance to use the Client/Server
    model of Rotor, or to look how we've done the Commodity Interface.
    Please @{i}don't@{ui} spread your improved versions of Rotor under the name
    of Rotor, because this may confuse the public and it's not fair.
@EndNode

